               <msContents>
                  <summary/>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <locus from="5ra" to ="24rb2"/>
                     <title>Maṣḥafa bǝrhān ‘Book of Light’ (different from Maṣḥafa bǝrhān ‘Book of
                        Light’ attributed to King Zarʾa Yāʿqob)</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                  <incipit xml:lang="gez">ንጽሕፍ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ ብርሃን፡ እንዘ፡ ትረድአነ፡ ኃይል፡ ከሀሊተ፡ ኵሉ፡ ግብር፡ እንተ፡ ዘቅድስት፡ </incipit>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <locus from="24rb5" to="38ra"/>
                     <title ref="LIT7831TemhertaHayAmh"/>
                     <textLang mainLang="am" otherLangs="gez"/> 
                     <incipit>ትምህርተ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ዘይደሉ፡ ይምሀርዎሙ፡ ለንኡሰ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ወያንቅህዎሙ፡ በዝንቱ፡ እምቅድመ፡ ጥምቀት፡ ወቍርባን። <gap reason="ellipsis" resp="MK"/> ሃይማኖት፡ ማየቻ፡ መተአመንው፡ በእግዚአብሔር፡ መተአመንም፡ እምነት፡ መከመቸትነው፡ ከተወላውሎ፡ ሕሊና፡ ጠቅሎ፡ በሐንድ፡ ልብ፡ 
                        መርምረነው፡ መርምሮም፡ ከአወቀው። <gap reason="ellipsis" resp="MK"/></incipit>
                     <note>The text was translated and its linguistic features were dealt with in <bibl><ptr target="bm:Cowley1974Amharic"/></bibl>.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i3">
                     <locus from="38rb" to="66vb"/>
                     <title ref="LIT4010Haymanotu"/>
                     <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i4">
                     <locus from="67ra" to="76vb1"/>
                     <title ref="LIT2471ToEulo"/>
                     <incipit>በስመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis" resp="MK"/> ጸሓፍነ፡ ዝንቱ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ በቍዔት፡ እምድርሳነ፡ ባሕሉ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ አባ፡ ወግሪስ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis" resp="MK"/> አእምር፡ ኦአኃው፡ ፍቁር፡ እስመ፡ አፍቅሮተ፡ ዛቲ፡ ዓለም፡
                        ተሀውክ፡ ልበ፡ ወታጸልም፡ ንጻሬ፡ ወታርኅቅ፡ እምእግዚአብሔር፡ ልዑል። አንተኒ፡ ኦአኃው፡ ግድፍ፡ እምኔከ፡ ወኢትፀመድ፡ ለፍትወት፡ <gap reason="ellipsis" resp="MK"/></incipit>
                     <note> cf. <ref type="mss" corresp="BLorient754#p1_i7.4"/> and <ref type="mss" corresp="EMML1387"/> <locus from="84b" to="86b"/></note>
                     <!--Check Grebaut ROC 19, 1914; GreTIsVat 576. Most likely this is an excerpt from Sentences by Evagrius -->
                     <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i5">
                     <locus from="76vb2" to="91va2"/>
                     <title ref="LIT2121OntheE"/>
                     <note> cf. <ref type="mss" corresp="BLorient757#ms_i2.11"/> and <ref type="mss" corresp="BLorient757#ms_i2.12"/>;  <ref type="mss" corresp="EMML1387"/>
                     <locus from="81a" to="84b"/></note>
                     <note>It contains the following parts:</note>
                     <note>V-1) Ba-ʾǝntä sǝssu kärś “On Gluttony” (<locus target="#76vb">76vb</locus> l. 6-78vb l.6)</note>
                     <note>V-2) Ba-ʾǝntä fǝqrä nǝwāy “On Avarice” (<locus target="#78vb">78vb</locus> l.6-80ra l.9)</note>
                     <note>V-3) Ba-ʾǝntä sǝbḥat bǝṭul “On Vainglory” (<locus target="#80ra">80ra</locus> l.9-81va l.7)</note>
                     <note>V-4) Ba-ʾǝntä tǝʿǝbit “On Pride” (<locus target="#81va">81va</locus>
                        l.7-83rb l.8)</note>
                     <note>V-5) Ba-ʾǝntä zǝmut “On Fornication” (<locus target="#83rb">83rb</locus>
                        l.8-86rb l.6)</note>
                     <note>V-6) Ba-ʾǝntä mäʿat “On Anger” (<locus target="#86rb">86rb</locus>
                        l.6-87vb l.10)</note>
                     <note>V-7) Ba-ʾǝntä ḥǝmamä lǝbb “On Akedia and on Sadness” (<locus target="#87vb">87vb</locus> l.10-91rb l.1).</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                     <explicit xml:id="coloph1" type="embedded">
                     <locus from="91rb" to="91va"/>
                     በሰላም፡ ተተርጐመ፡ እምዓረቢ፡ ለግዕዝ:: በመዋዕለ፡ ንጉሥነ፡ መፍቀሬ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡
                     ገላውዴዎስ:: እምአመ፡ ነግሠ፡ በ፲ወ፫ዓመት፡ ስብሐት፡ ለእግዚአብሔር: ወትረ፡ እስከ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም:
                     አሜን::
                     <quote xml:lang="en">It was translated in peace from Arabic into Gǝʿǝz; in the time of our
                     King, the lover of God, Galāwdewos; in the 13th year of his reign, glory to
                     God always until eternity, Amen.</quote></explicit>
                  </msItem>
                  
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i6">
                        <locus from="91va5" to="94vb"/>
                  <title>Excerpt from the Collectio
                  Monastica ch. 20, 143-145 (Nagara ʾabaw za-mänäkosat “Saying(s) of the Fathers
                  of Monks”</title> 
                        <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                        <note>- Text VI: cf. V. ARRAS, Collectio Monastica, Louvain 1963 (CSCO 238, 239
                           [SAe 45, 46]), ch. 20,<ref type="mss" corresp="ES143145">143-145</ref>.</note>
                     </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i7">
                     <locus from="95ra" to="104ra"/>
                     <title ref="LIT0370Malke"/>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">እምአፈ፡ ልቡና፡ ዘወፅኡ፡ ልሳናተ፡ ጥበብ፡ ወቃል፡ ጽልመተ፡ ሕሊናየ፡ ይብራኅ፡ በመጽሔቶሙ፡</incipit>
                     <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i8">
                     <locus from="104rb" to="110rb"/>
                     <title>Ba-sägid sǝbḥat la-zǝkra sǝmǝkä... “Through worshipping (is) glory to the
                        memory of your name...”</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">በሰጊድ፡ ስብሐት፡ ለዝክረ፡ ስምከ፡ ሰላም፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ዋሕድ። በከመ፡ ነገረ፡ ወልደ፡ ነጐድጓድ። ፀዓዳ፡ ከመ፡ በረድ፡ በሰጊድ፡ ስብሐት፡ ወለርእስከ፡ ሰላም፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ብሩክ፡ </incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="gez">መሐሪት፡ ዓይንከ፡ ትትመየጠነ፡ እንከ። በእንተ፡ ሥጋከ፡ ወደምከ፡ ስእለተ፡ ሕዝብከ፡ ስማዕ፡ ኢይኩን፡ በከ። ተወከፎን፡ ነግሀ፡ ወሰርከ፡፡ አሜን።</explicit>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i9">
                     <locus from="111ra" to="111vb7"></locus>
                     <title>Malkǝʾa śǝʿǝl “Image of
                        the Icon” </title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">እሰግድ፡ ለኪ፡ ከመ፡ ኃጢአትየ፡ ታስተስርዪ። ማርያም፡ ንግሥት፡ ቅድመ፡ ዓይነ፡ ኵሉ፡ ጸላዪ። ሥእለ፡ አድኅኖ፡ ሥዕልኪ፡ እንተ፡ ትሰመዩ።</incipit>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i10">
                     <locus from="111vb9" to="114va11"></locus>
                     <title>Ba-sägid sǝbḥat la-mäʿaza sǝmǝkä...
                        “In worship is glory to the odor of your name...”</title>
                     <note>(cp. Mss. EMML nos. 1095, 1246, 1380 etc.)</note>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i11">
