                              <abbr>ሠ፡</abbr> for <expan>ሠረቀ፡</expan> (e.g., <locus target="#152rb #153rab #155va"/>)</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Divine names; first component of the name of the
                           donor; two or three lines (alternating with black lines) of the incipit of texts from <ref target="#ms_i1"/> to <ref target="#ms_i3"/>, <ref target="#ms_i8"/> from <ref target="#ms_i12"/> to <ref target="#ms_i16"/>;
                           two initial lines of the incipit of texts from <ref target="#ms_i4"/> to <ref target="#ms_i7"/>; two initial lines of
                           the sections of <ref target="#ms_i2"/>; supplication formula on <locus target="118rb"/>; word <foreign xml:lang="gez">salām</foreign>
                           ‘greeting’ and its abbreviations in <ref target="#ms_i7"/>, <ref target="#ms_i12"/>and <ref target="#ms_i13"/>; phrases
                           ba-sagid sǝbḥat ‘through worshipping (is) glory’ and maḥarit ‘merciful’
                           in <ref target="#ms_i8"/>; a few words such as <foreign xml:lang="gez">tafassǝḥi</foreign> ‘rejoice’, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ʾanti</foreign> ‘you’,
                           <foreign xml:lang="gez">kʷǝllomu</foreign> ‘all of them’, <foreign xml:lang="gez">tanabayu</foreign> ‘they prophesied’ in <ref target="#ms_i16"/>; elements
